A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Michele Riggs; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Michele Riggs has diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours
3 of her time, talents, and energy toward the betterment of her community and state, as
4 evidenced dramatically by her more than two decades of superlative service with Wellstar
5 Health System; and
6 WHEREAS, she began her exemplary career with Wellstar Health System in 2000, serving
7 at the Cobb and Kennestone hospitals as a board-certified lactation consultant before
8 becoming the manager of Maternal Infant Support Services in 2005 and later assuming the
9 role of director of Women's Health Patient Education and Support Services; and
10 WHEREAS, throughout her career, she has led numerous initiatives to improve breastfeeding
11 quality outcomes, including securing Baby Friendly Hospital Designation for Wellstar
12 Kennestone in 2017, establishing a milk depot, implementing human donor milk
13 supplementation, and creating employee pumping stations across the system; and
14 WHEREAS, she has been instrumental in standardizing women's education, including
15 perinatal education classes and support groups, and implementing system-wide patient
